The paper deals with a problem of covering a biset-family by a minimum-cost set of directed edges, which involves graph theory and optimization. The paper also mentions network design problems, which suggests a connection to computer networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.NE (Network Economics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
